The paper presents a machine learning model for multi-view learning, which involves learning from multiple sources of data. This is a common problem in several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on kernel-based methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.SI.
